# CSV Parser - Usage Examples

This document provides detailed examples of how to use the CSV Parser library.

## Table of Contents
1. [Basic Usage](#basic-usage)
2. [Quoted Fields](#quoted-fields)
3. [Custom Delimiters](#custom-delimiters)
4. [Type Coercion](#type-coercion)
5. [Error Handling](#error-handling)
6. [Filtering](#filtering)
7. [Aggregations](#aggregations)
8. [Real-World Examples](#real-world-examples)

## Basic Usage

### Simple CSV Parsing

```javascript
const { parseCSV } = require('./csv-parser');

const csv = `name,age,city
Alice,30,New York
Bob,25,London
Charlie,35,Paris`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.headers);
// Output: ['name', 'age', 'city']

console.log(result.rows);
// Output: [
//   { name: 'Alice', age: 30, city: 'New York' },
//   { name: 'Bob', age: 25, city: 'London' },
//   { name: 'Charlie', age: 35, city: 'Paris' }
// ]
```

### Single Column CSV

```javascript
const csv = `product
Apple
Banana
Orange`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows);
// Output: [
//   { product: 'Apple' },
//   { product: 'Banana' },
//   { product: 'Orange' }
// ]
```

## Quoted Fields

### Fields Containing Commas

```javascript
const csv = `name,address,city
Alice,"123 Main St, Apt 4",New York
Bob,"456 Oak Ave, Suite 200",London
Charlie,"789 Pine Rd, Unit 3",Paris`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].address);
// Output: "123 Main St, Apt 4"
```

### Multiple Quoted Fields

```javascript
const csv = `name,phone,email
Alice,"555-1234, ext 5","alice@example.com, Inc."
Bob,"555-5678, ext 2","bob@test.org, Ltd."`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].phone);
// Output: "555-1234, ext 5"

console.log(result.rows[0].email);
// Output: "alice@example.com, Inc."
```

### Escaped Quotes in Fields

```javascript
const csv = `name,quote
Alice,"She said ""Hello World"""
Bob,"He replied ""How are you?"""
Charlie,"I said ""Never mind"""`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].quote);
// Output: She said "Hello World"

console.log(result.rows[1].quote);
// Output: He replied "How are you?"
```

### Multiline Fields

```javascript
const csv = `name,description
Product A,"High quality item
Made from premium materials
Excellent durability"
Product B,"Budget option
Good value
Standard quality"`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].description);
// Output: High quality item
// Made from premium materials
// Excellent durability
```

## Custom Delimiters

### Semicolon Delimiter

```javascript
const csv = `name;age;email
Alice;30;alice@example.com
Bob;25;bob@example.com
Charlie;35;charlie@example.com`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, { delimiter: ';' });

console.log(result.rows[0].email);
// Output: alice@example.com
```

### Tab Delimiter

```javascript
const csv = `name\tage\tposition
Alice\t30\tManager
Bob\t25\tDeveloper
Charlie\t35\tDesigner`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, { delimiter: '\t' });

console.log(result.rows[0].position);
// Output: Manager
```

### Pipe Delimiter

```javascript
const csv = `id|product|price
1|Apple|1.99
2|Banana|0.59
3|Orange|0.75`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, { delimiter: '|' });

console.log(result.rows[1].product);
// Output: Banana
```

### CRLF Line Endings

```javascript
const csv = 'name,age\r\nAlice,30\r\nBob,25\r\nCharlie,35';

const result = parseCSV(csv, { lineSeparator: '\r\n' });

console.log(result.rows.length);
// Output: 3
```

### Custom Quote Character

```javascript
const csv = `name,city
Alice,'New York'
Bob,'Los Angeles'
Charlie,'San Francisco'`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, { quote: "'" });

console.log(result.rows[0].city);
// Output: New York
```

### Multiple Custom Options

```javascript
const csv = `name;age;email
'Alice';'30';'alice@example.com'
'Bob';'25';'bob@example.com'`;

const result = parseCSV(csv, {
  delimiter: ';',
  quote: "'",
  lineSeparator: '\n'
});

console.log(result.rows[0].name);
// Output: Alice
```

## Type Coercion

### Automatic Number Detection

```javascript
const csv = `product,quantity,price
Apple,10,1.99
Banana,5,0.59
Orange,8,0.75`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].quantity);           // 10 (number)
console.log(typeof result.rows[0].quantity);    // "number"

console.log(result.rows[0].price);              // 1.99 (number)
console.log(typeof result.rows[0].price);       // "number"
```

### Negative Numbers

```javascript
const csv = `transaction,amount
Purchase,-50.00
Refund,-25.50
Sale,100.00
Credit,-10.00`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].amount);    // -50
console.log(result.rows[2].amount);    // 100
```

### Scientific Notation

```javascript
const csv = `measurement,value
Small,1e-5
Medium,1e0
Large,1e5`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].value);    // 0.00001
console.log(result.rows[1].value);    // 1
console.log(result.rows[2].value);    // 100000
```

### Boolean Conversion

```javascript
const csv = `feature,enabled,disabled
Feature A,true,false
Feature B,TRUE,FALSE
Feature C,True,False`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].enabled);           // true (boolean)
console.log(result.rows[0].disabled);          // false (boolean)
console.log(typeof result.rows[0].enabled);    // "boolean"

// All forms are case-insensitive
console.log(result.rows[1].enabled);           // true
console.log(result.rows[2].enabled);           // true
```

### Null Conversion

```javascript
const csv = `name,middle,nickname
Alice,,Alice
Bob,Robert,Bobby
Charlie,null,Chuck
Diana,Marie,NULL`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows[0].middle);     // null (from empty string)
console.log(result.rows[2].nickname);   // null (from "null")
console.log(result.rows[3].nickname);   // null (from "NULL")
console.log(result.rows[1].middle);     // "Robert" (string)
```

### Mixed Types in Column

```javascript
const csv = `id,value
1,42
2,hello
3,true
4,
5,3.14`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(typeof result.rows[0].value);   // "number" (42)
console.log(typeof result.rows[1].value);   // "string" ("hello")
console.log(typeof result.rows[2].value);   // "boolean" (true)
console.log(result.rows[3].value);          // null
console.log(typeof result.rows[4].value);   // "number" (3.14)
```

## Error Handling

### Handling Unclosed Quotes

```javascript
const csv = `name,description
Alice,"Good person
Bob,Nice guy`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows);           // [{ name: 'Bob', description: 'Nice guy' }]
console.log(result.errors);         // [{ row: 1, message: 'Unclosed quote in line' }]
```

### Field Count Mismatch

```javascript
const csv = `name,age,city
Alice,30,New York
Bob,25
Charlie,35,Paris,Extra`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

console.log(result.rows);           // [{ name: 'Charlie', age: 35, city: 'Paris' }]
console.log(result.errors);         // [
                                    // { row: 1, message: 'Expected 3 fields, got 2' },
                                    // { row: 2, message: 'Expected 3 fields, got 4' }
                                    // ]
```

### Checking for Errors

```javascript
const csv = `name,age
Alice,30,Extra
Bob,25
Charlie,35`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

if (result.errors.length > 0) {
  console.log('Parsing encountered errors:');
  result.errors.forEach(error => {
    console.log(`  Row ${error.row}: ${error.message}`);
  });
}

console.log(`Successfully parsed ${result.rows.length} rows`);
```

## Filtering

### Filter by Numeric Condition

```javascript
const csv = `name,age,salary
Alice,30,50000
Bob,25,45000
Charlie,35,60000
Diana,28,52000`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Get employees over 30
const over30 = result.filter(row => row.age > 30);
console.log(over30.rows[0].name);    // Charlie

// Get high earners
const highEarners = result.filter(row => row.salary > 50000);
console.log(highEarners.rows[0].name);    // Charlie
```

### Filter by String Match

```javascript
const csv = `name,department,status
Alice,Sales,Active
Bob,Engineering,Active
Charlie,Sales,Inactive
Diana,Engineering,Active`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Get sales team
const sales = result.filter(row => row.department === 'Sales');
console.log(sales.rows.length);    // 2

// Get active employees
const active = result.filter(row => row.status === 'Active');
console.log(active.rows.length);   // 3
```

### Chained Filters

```javascript
const csv = `name,department,salary,active
Alice,Sales,50000,true
Bob,Engineering,60000,true
Charlie,Sales,45000,false
Diana,Engineering,55000,true
Eve,Sales,52000,true`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Get active sales employees earning over 50000
const filtered = result
  .filter(row => row.active === true)
  .filter(row => row.department === 'Sales')
  .filter(row => row.salary > 50000);

console.log(filtered.rows.length);    // 1 (Eve)
console.log(filtered.rows[0].name);   // Eve
```

### Complex Filter Logic

```javascript
const csv = `product,category,price,inStock
Apple,Fruit,1.99,true
Banana,Fruit,0.59,true
Milk,Dairy,3.99,false
Cheese,Dairy,5.99,true
Bread,Bakery,2.99,true`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Get in-stock dairy products under $5
const filtered = result.filter(row => 
  row.inStock === true && 
  row.category === 'Dairy' && 
  row.price < 5
);

console.log(filtered.rows[0].product);    // Cheese
```

